### Magic Items A-Z

#### Arcane Lockbox
*Wondrous item, rarity varies*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*Devised by skilled tinkerers, there a few things more deviously complex than an arcane lockbox.* 
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

This 4-inch wide puzzle box displays complex runes which change each dawn. The box cannot be destroyed except through a *disintegrate* or *wish* spell.

After three uninterrupted hours of concentration, roll three consecutive Intelligence checks, the DC of which depends on the rarity of the puzzlebox.

Rarity      | DC
------------|----
Uncommon    | 12
Rare        | 14
Very Rare   | 16
Legendary   | 18

If one of the three checks fail, the box "locks" and the puzzle cannot be attempted until it resets at the next dawn. A *knock* spell can reduce the number of checks to two, but no less than two. The last person to successfully open a puzzle box can access it with a touch of their hand. They also receive a mental *alarm* whenever a puzzle attempts fails (provided they are on the same plane).

Each box can contain a single item, no bigger than a 5-foot cube, which appears once the box collapses open. The item within is protected from *scrying*, *detect magic*, and similar effects.

#### Arcanist's Circlet
*Wondrous item, uncommon (requires attunement)*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*Affixed with a black opal, this antique circlet was commonly worn by the Elven sorcerers of old. Much of their strange magic still lingers within.*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

While wearing the circlet, you know the *magic missile* spell and always have it prepared.

***Mote Magic.*** The circlet has three small motes of arcane energy orbiting your head. As a bonus action, you can fire one of the motes at a target you can see within 120 feet. Make an attack roll with proficiency using your Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma modifier (your choice). 

On a hit, the mote deals force damage equal to half your level, rounded down (to a minimum of 1 damage). Once the motes are used up, they replenish after 1 minute.

#### Archivist's Spectacles
*Wondrous item, rare (requires attunement)*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*Ornate frames surround these large crystal lenses, both etched with delicate hair-line symbols across the surface. These spectacles are especially prized by apprentice wizards, cramming for their upcoming exam.*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

While wearing these spectacles, you have advantage on Arcana and History checks, can read three times faster than normal, and are under the effects of *comprehend languages* (written languages only).

#### Bag of Treats [WIP]
*Wondrous item, common*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*Flavor Text.*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

This belt pouch appears empty and has 10 charges. While holding the pouch, you can use an action to expend 1 of its charges, speak the name of a type of beast, and pull out a small biscuit flavored and scented to appeal to that creature. The pouch regains 1d6 + 4 expended charges at dawn.

#### Banner of the Last Stand
*Weapon (spear), legendary (requires attunement)*

*When the first heroes stood up against the oppressors of the weak, they wove this banner so that future generations would remember the importance of selflessness and true bravery.*

You have a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon.

As an action, you can thrust the spear into the ground, and with a with a battle cry, cause the magnificent banner to unfurl.

All those who hear you may immediately spend a reaction to respond to your call and gain a point of inspiration, or a d12 inspiration die to use on an attack, ability check, or saving throw. The banner depicts the heroic deeds of each who respond to the call.

***Aura of Heroes.*** In addition, all those who've responded to the initial battle cry have +1 on attack rolls and advantage on saving throws against the frightened condition whilst within 30 feet of the banner.

The banner cannot be removed, altered or destroyed by anyone or anything short of a wish spell. After one hour of use, its effect ends and cannot be used again until 100 years have passed. 

#### Book of the Dead [WIP]
*Wondrous item, rare (requires attunement)*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*Flavor Text.*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

***Spells.*** While holding the book, you can use an action to expend some of its charges to cast one of the following spells from it, using your spell save DC and spellcasting ability: *animate dead* (3 charges), *circle of death* (6 charges), *create undead* (6 charges), *danse macabre* ^XGE^ (5 charges), *death ward* (4 charges), *false life* (1 charge per spell level, up to 5th), *feign death* (3 charges), *finger of death* (7 charges), *gentle repose* (2 charges), *life transference* ^XGE^ (3 charges), *negative energy flood* ^XGE^ (5 charges), *raise dead* (5 charges), *revivify* (3 charges), *soul cage* (6 charges), *speak with dead* (3 charges), *summon undead* ^TCE^ (3 charges), *vampiric touch* (3 charges).

You can use an action to cast one of the following spells from the book without using any charges: *spare the dying* and *toll the dead*. While attuned this book, you also add the above spells to your class's spell list, as well as spells and cantrips known.

