Playing this flute summons a cloud of illusory butterflies. As an action, you can make a DC 10

#### Captain's Tricorn
*Wondrous item, rare (requires attunement)*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*When stealing ships, It used to be tradition amongst pirates to claim the unlucky captain’s hat. The bigger the hat, the better! However, this led to a very unpleasant epidemic of sea-fairing head-lice.*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

The hat holds 8 charges and regains 2 charges each dawn. If worn aboard a sea vessel, it gains 1d6 + 2 charges instead.

***Captain's Orders.*** You can expend one charge as an action to cast *command*, or issue a *mass suggestion* to multiple creatures for 3 hours, spending two charges per target (spell save DC 14).

#### Compass of Homesickness
*Wondrous item, common*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*Commonly used by sailors and soldiers, this small device lets them carry a little bit of home with them, and to always know which way to walk to get there.*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

This compass has a small compartment under the dial, which can be filled with earth, sand, dirt, or small pebbles. The compass dial features two needles. The small needle always points towards the magnetic north. However, the large needle always points towards the location the material in the compartment was taken from.

If the compartment is empty, filled with any other type of material, or material taken from another plane of existence, the needle spins around aimlessly.

\pagebreak

#### Decanter of False Youth
*Wondrous item, very rare*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*Created by a vampire sorceress, this alabaster jug depicts beautiful nymphs on its side. However, water poured into it turns to blood and the nymphs transform into grisly skeletons. Some say the gift it grants has too high a price.*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

This jug can hold up to five pints. Water poured into it turns to blood. Drinking 1 pint from the decanter grants 1d4 + 4 temporary hit points to the drinker, lasting for one hour. While you have these temporary hit points, you appear visibly younger and more beautiful. The jug can create up to ten pints of blood a day.

***Cursed.*** All who drink from the jug become vulnerable to radiant damage and gain resistance to healing until the curse is lifted.

#### Doomslayer [WIP]
*Weapon (greatsword), legendary (requires attunement)*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

When found, this weapon appears to be a hilt of dark metal. 

***Among the Dark.*** While grasping the hilt, you can use a bonus action to cause a blade of blazingly hot, seemingly solid light to spring into existence, or make the blade disappear. While the blade exists, the following applies:
- The blade sheds bright light in a 20 foot radius and dim light for an additional 20 feet.
- You have a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this weapon.
- The weapon deals radiant damage instead of slashing damage.
- The weapon deals an additional 2d6 fire damage on a hit, plus 2d6 radiant damage if the target is a fiend.

***The Chosen.*** This weapon imbues its wielder with incredible strength and fortitude. While attuned to this weapon, your Strength score is increased by 2, to a maximum of 22. 

Additionally, your maximum hit point total is increased to the amount it would be if you had rolled the highest number on each Hit Die. For example, the hit point maximum of a 12th-level barbarian with a Constitution bonus of +3 would become 180.

***Raze Hell.*** While attuned to this weapon, you know Abyssal and Infernal, and you have advantage on all attack rolls made against fiends and on ability checks made to track or recall information about them.

***[Blade Break]*** On a critical hit against a fiend, you can attempt to embed the blade into the target. Roll a d20

***Sentience.*** Doomslayer is a sentient neutral weapon with an Intelligence of 11, a Wisdom of 14, and a Charisma of 19. It has hearing and darkvision out to a range of 120 feet. The weapon communicates by transmitting emotion to the creature carrying or wielding it.

***Personality.*** Doomslayer's sole purpose is to end the lives of fiends and destroy their works. It remains silent

***Cursed.*** While attuned to this weapon, you gain an undying hatred against all fiends. If you ever willingly help or make a deal with a fiend, unless doing so would lead to the destruction of more fiends or protect innocents from their wrath, you immediately lose attunement

#### Druid's Bag [WIP]
*Wondrous item, very rare*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

A used bag of holding modified by a druid.

Inside the bag are two pocket dimensions, one a garden with many plants used for components and potions. 

The other is a library filled with books and other type of materials such as gems, bone dust, alcohol, clay, iron, phosphorus and other non plant based items (most of these materials are in bottles with handy labels). 

A creature can survive and breathe in these two pocket dimensions and can enter or exit through the bag.

#### Elixir of Dominant Person [WIP]
*Potion, very rare*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*Flavor text.*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

When you drink this potion, for 1 hour you can cast *command* (save DC 15) at will. During that hour, your personality becomes self-assured and authoritative and you gain advantage on Wisdom saving throws. This potion's bitter black liquid has an intoxicating aroma. Strangely, it never quite touches the bottom of the glass.

#### Five (Round? Second?) Energy
*Potion, RARITY*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*ALL MY SENSES ARE AS ONE! THE WEAVE OF REALITY UNRAVELS BEFORE ME!*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

You gain an additional action each turn for the duration, but become absolutely manic at the same time. At the end of the potion, you have a heart attack and gain exhaustion.

