#### Potion of Swimming [WIP]
*Potion, common*

When you drink this potion, you gain a swimming speed equal to your walking speed for 1 hour. During this time, you have advantage on Strength (Athletics) checks you make to swim. The potion is sea-green, with its surface continually moving in small crested waves.

#### Rift Breaker [WIP]
*Weapon (spear), rare (requires attunement)*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*This tip of this spear, looking primitive at a glance, is crafted from an unknown crystal. Its ability to strike targets blindsided is immeasurably useful.*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

You gain a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon.

*dimension door*

***Rift Strike.*** (4/day) As an action, you can momentarily pierce the veil between dimensions, creating two connecting rifts in the air just big enough for the spear to pass through. You may make a melee attack against a creature you can see within 60 feet from any direction. You may also throw the spear in this way, changing the trajectory of the spear to whatever direction the connecting rift faces.

***Escape Rift.*** As an action, you can drive the butt of the spear into the ground, destroying the spear and instantly creating a 10 foot diameter *teleportation circle*. Lasting 1 round, all who enter the circle are teleported to an unknown location determined by the GM.

#### Ring of Perfume
*Ring, common*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*Once popular amongst members of high society, these rings famously fell into disuse after many jealous pranks ensued.*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

This ring has 10 charges. You can use an action to cause expend a charge, causing it to emit any kind of scent or smell the wearer wishes in a 5-foot radius, centered on the ring. The effect lasts for 1 hour, or until you use a charge to change the scent.

\pagebreak

#### Scimitar of the Sirocco
*Weapon (scimitar), very rare (requires attunement)*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*Rust and wear covers the blade of this Khopesh sword. As you swing it, it moves effortlessly through the air, leaving behind a thin trail of sand...Suddenly, your mouth grows inexplicably dry.*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

You gain a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon. In addition, you can make one attack with it as a bonus action on each of your turns.

This sword scores a critical hit on a roll of 19 or 20. On a critical hit, the sword drains moisture from the target, inflicting 2 levels of exhaustion and removing 2 levels of exhaustion from the wielder.

***Cursed.*** All water and drink that passes your lips turns to sand. Every day, you suffer 1 level of exhaustion which cannot be recovered through normal rest.

#### Soldier's Trinket [WIP]
*Wondrous item, common*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*Flavor text.*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

While carrying this trinket, when you fail (but not critically fail) a death saving throw, you can turn it into a success. Once you use this ability, the trinket becomes inactive for seven days and you cannot benefit from another until the end of your next long rest.

#### Spirit Lantern
*Wondrous item, uncommon*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*Containing the dying breath of a unknown entity, this lantern is often used by Funerary priests to identify the fallen bodies on the battlefield.*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

This lantern emits a cold, dim blue light in a 20 foot radius. If you shine this light on deceased remains for 1 minute, you can cause ghostly illusions of the dead creatures to manifest.

These illusions hover above the remains and act out the last five minutes of the creature's life. This effect is silent and shows the dead as they appeared in life, depicting any items they carried. It does not, however, reveal any others who may have been present at the time of the creature's death.

#### Staff of the Acolyte [WIP]
*Staff, uncommon (requires attunement by a cleric)*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

The staff has 4 charges. While holding it, you can expend a charge as an action to cast *bless* or *cure wounds*, using your spellcasting modifier. You can also use an action to cast *spare the dying* or *thaumaturgy*. 

The staff regains 1d4 charges at dawn. If you expend the last charge, roll a d20. On a 1, the staff crumbles to dust and is destroyed.

#### Staff of the Apprentice
*Staff, uncommon (requires attunement by a sorcerer, warlock, or wizard)*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*Young wizards often craft their own staves as a symbol of their completed studies. These staves are limited in power and vary in appearance: from the subtle to the outlandishly garish.*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

There are eight varieties of this staff, containing two 1st-level spells from one of the eight schools of magic. The GM chooses the type or determines it randomly from the options below.

d8  | School        | Spells
----|---------------|-----------
1   | Abjuration    | *protection from evil and good*, *shield*
2   | Conjuration   | *fog cloud*, *grease*
3   | Divination    | *comprehend languages*, *detect magic*
4   | Enchantment   | *charm person*, *sleep*
5   | Evocation     | *burning hands*, *magic missile*
6   | Illusion      | *color spray*, *silent image*
7   | Necromancy    | *cause fear* ^XGE^, *ray of sickness*
8   | Transmutation | *feather fall*, *jump*

The staff has 5 charges. While holding it, you can use an action to expend 1 of its charges to cast one of the spells contained within it, using your spell save DC. The staff regains 1d4 + 1 expended charges daily at dawn.

Once a week, you can replace one spell within the staff with another 1st spell you know from the same school.

#### Staff of Curses [WIP]
[A warlock staff.]

#### Staff of the Earth [WIP]

✦ *earthen spike* (3 charges), *erupting earth* (3 charges), ✦ *lava burst* (2 charges), *investiture of stone* ^XGE^ (6 charges), *wall of sand* ^XGE^ (3 charges), *wall of stone* (5 charges)

#### Staff of the Flames [WIP]
*flame strike* (5 charges), *investiture of flame* ^XGE^ (6 charges), *wall of fire* (4 charges)


#### Staff of the Novice [WIP]
*Staff, uncommon (requires attunement by a sorcerer or wizard)*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

This staff has 4 charges. While holding it, you can expend a charge as an action to cast *magic missile*, or as a reaction to cast *shield*. You can also use an action to cast *light* (targeting the gem in the staff's head) or *prestidigitation*.

The staff regains 1d4 charges at dawn. If you expend the last charge, roll a d20. On a 1, the staff crumbles to dust and is destroyed.

#### Staff of the Waves [WIP]
*control water* (4 charges), *investiture of ice* ^XGE^ (6 charges), *sleet storm* (3 charges), *tidal wave* ^XGE^ (3 charges), *wall of ice* (6 charges), *wall of water* ^XGE^ (3 charges), *water breathing* (3 charges), *water walk* (3 charges)

Swim speed, cold damage

\pagebreak

#### Staff of the Winds [WIP]
*Staff, very rare (requires attunement by a shaman)*

While attuned to the staff, when you fall, you descend 60 feet per round and take no damage from falling. 

The staff has 20 charges for the following properties. The staff regains 2d8 + 4 expended charges daily at dawn. If you expend the last charge, roll a d20. On a 1, the staff retains the Inured to the Elements property but loses all others.

***Inured to the Elements.*** While holding the staff, when you fall, you descend 60 feet per round and take no damage from falling. Additionally, you are acclimatized to high altitudes and are unaffected by strong winds.

***Flight.*** You can expend 1 charge from the staff while holding it to grant yourself a fly speed equal to your movement speed for 1 hour.

***Spells.*** While holding this staff, you can use an action to expend 1 or more of its charges to cast one of the following spells from it, using your spell save DC and spell attack bonus: *call lightning* (3 charges), *conjure elemental* (air elemental, 5 charges), *control winds* ^XGE^ (5 charges), *dust devil* ^XGE^ (2 charges), *feather fall* (1 charge), *fly* (3 charges), *gust of wind* (2 charges), *investiture of wind* ^XGE^ (6 charges), *skywrite* ^XGE^ (2 charges), *storms sphere* ^XGE^ (4 charges), *thunderwave* (1 charge), *warding wind* (3 charges), *wind walk* (6 charges), or *wind wall* (3 charges). 

#### Staff of the Woodsman [WIP]
*Staff, uncommon (requires attunement by a druid)*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

The staff has 4 charges and is under a continual *shillelagh* spell. While holding it, you can expend a charge as an action to cast *entangle* or *goodberry*, using your spell save DC. The goodberries sprout from the head of the staff. You can also use an action to cast *druidcraft*. 

The staff regains 1d4 charges at dawn. If you expend the last charge, roll a d20. On a 1, the staff crumbles to dust and is destroyed.

#### Stellarnight Dreamoire [WIP]
*Wondrous item, rare (requires attunement by a wizard)*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

This book is covered in a very comfortable cushion and pillow. You can use this book as a spellcasting focus for your wizard spells. When found, it contains the spells *alarm*, *sleep*, *phantasmal force*, *catnap*, *leomund's tiny hut*, *mordenkainen's private sanctum*, and *dream*.

When you take a long rest using this grimoire as a pillow, you dream of the future. When you finish the long rest, roll a d20 and record the number rolled. You can replace any attack roll, saving throw, or ability check made by you or a creature that you can see with this foretelling roll. The fortunetelling roll can only be used once. When you finish a long rest, you lose it if you did not use it.

#### The Minmaxe
*Weapon (any axe), legendary (requires attunement)*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*"Sure, he's not the best conversationalist. And I do admit the constant drooling does get annoying. But I swear, I once saw him pick up a dragon and throw it at another dragon."*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

You have a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon.

Each time you complete a long rest, you can decrease an ability score and its maximum by up to two points. If you do, you may increase a different ability score and its maximum by two points. Your ability scores and their maximums revert to their original value if you unattune from this weapon.

#### Tipsy Bonk-Bonk [WIP]
*Weapon (warhammer), uncommon*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

You have a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this magic weapon.

The warhammer has 6 charges and regains 1d6 charges at dawn. You can spend any number of charges to produce a delicious fresh beer from it, 1 charge being equivalent to 1 liter.

Also, when you hit a creature, you can expend 2 charges to force the creature to make a DC 14 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, it is drunk for 1 minute, and illusory birds appear around its head. While drunk, it is considered poisoned and must roll a d6 every time it moves more than 5 feet. On a 5, it must use all its movement to move in a random direction. On a 6, it falls prone before moving.

#### Tombstone Shield [WIP]
*Shield, rare (requires attunement)*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

When a humanoid creature dies within 15 feet of you while carrying this shield, you can use your reaction to absorb its spirit. The name of the creature is carved on the shield, for a maximum of 10 names. When found, the shield has 1d10 names carved on it.

When you take damage when using the shield, you can use your reaction to call forth any number of spirits from the shield and reduce the damage by 1d10 + 1 per spirit. Alternatively, you can cast *speak with dead* on one of the names, without needing the body or expending a spell slot. After using either of these effects, the name disappears from the shield and the spirit is gone.

***Cursed.*** If you die and there are less than 10 names inscribed on the shield, your spirit becomes trapped in it. Your name appears on the shield and you can't be resurrected in any way unless the shield is cleansed by a *greater restoration* spell.

#### Viper Whip
*Weapon (whip), rare (requires attunement)*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*This snake-headed whip seems to curl and twist on its own accord. Occasionally it even sheds its own skin...*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

You gain a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made using the weapon. On a hit, the weapon deals an extra 1d6 poison damage.

On a successful hit, you can cause the viper head of this whip to bite a target creature. For the next 12 hours, you are able to determine which direction the creature is within 1000 meters, and whether they are dead or alive.

\pagebreak

#### Wand of Bubbles
*Wand, common*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*There has been a few cases where this simple toy has been mistaken for a wand of fireballs...much to the user’s chagrin.*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

As an action, you can cause harmless bubbles to stream from the end of this wand.

#### Wand of Lights
*Wand, common*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*This wand is a common tool found in wizard towers, used to read books late in the night, light up dark corners of a library, indicate certain runes on lecture boards...and keep cat familiars entertained.*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

As an action, you can use the wand to create one of the following effects:
- The tip of the wand lights up, shedding bright light in a 30-foot radius and dim light for an additional 30 feet.
- The wand casts bright light in a 60-foot cone and dim light for an additional 60 feet.
- A needle-thin line of light is cast from the tip of the wand, creating a small dot of light up to 1 mile away.

#### Wand of Spider Summoning
*Wand, uncommon (requires attunement)*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*The mandibles on this unnerving wand twitch and chitter. The hairs on your arm stand on end as you grasp it.*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

This wand has 8 charges. As an action, you can expend one or more charges to summon one of the following for 1 minute: a giant spider (3 charges), a spider swarm (2 charges), or a spider (1 charge). Each spider obeys your verbal commands, and in combat, they act on your turn each round. The GM has the statistics for these creatures and resolves their actions and movement.

The wand regains 1d6 + 2 expended charges each day at dusk. If you expend the wand's last charge, roll a d20. On a 1, the wand turns into a spider and scuttles away.

#### Weapon of Searing Strikes [WIP]
*Weapon (any), rarity varies (requires attunement)*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

A weapon that can be used like a wand, to cast a smite spell.

#### Wild Dude
*Potion, uncommon*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*For most people, this chaotic drink has a different flavour each time it is sipped. Bizarrely, sorcerers can only taste pineapple.*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

This small bottle of liquor appears to be a multicolored tropical drink, continually shifting in appearance. When you drink it as an action, immediately roll on the Wild Magic Surge table (located on page 104 in the Player's Handbook).

#### Winter's Howl
*Weapon (greataxe), very rare (requires attunement)*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*Said to contain the spirits of three winter wolves, this axe’s cry sends a chill through your enemies...literally!*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

You have a +2 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with this weapon, which deals an additional 1d4 cold damage on a hit.

***Howl of Winter.*** As an action, you can cause the axe to emit a chilling howl (which can be heard up to 300 feet away), freezing the air around you.

All other creatures within a 15-foot radius suffer 1d6 cold damage and must succeed on a DC 16 Strength saving throw. On a failed save, they become paralyzed, entombed in a pillar of ice for 1 minute. At the end of each of its turns, a frozen target can attempt another Strength save, ending the effect on a success.

Attacking the frozen creature ends the paralysis effect and deals an additional 1d6 cold damage.

#### Witch's Ring
*Ring, uncommon (requires attunement)*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

*Found in many forms, these rings always have a particular creature featured in its design. Many witches and nefarious warlocks have escaped capture with this ring’s help.*
<div style='margin-top:-4px;'></div>

This ring allows you to take on the form of a particular beast as an action, or back as a bonus action. You can transform for up to 2 hours, all at once or for shorter periods of time, each transformation using a minimum of 1 minute from the duration. Treat this as though you transformed through the *polymorph* spell, except you retain your hit points between forms.

When you first attune to the ring, roll a d8 on the table below to determine which form you take. The GM has the creature's statistics, which can be found in Appendix A of the Monster Manual. The ring regains any expended duration at dusk; at that time, roll a d8 to determine which new form the ring provides. If you are a warlock or druid, you can choose which form you transform into whenever you use the ring.

| d8 | Creature  | d8 | Creature  |
|----|-----------|----|-----------|
|  1 | Cat       |  5 | Rat       |
|  2 | Frog      |  6 | Raven     |
|  3 | Bat       |  7 | Spider    |
|  4 | Owl       |  8 | Goat      |

